                                                          cern.colt.matrix.DoubleMatrix2D features,
                                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Object> parameters)
                                                   throws GggpExceptionImpl
The function calculates for each derivation (d) that belongs to "individuals", the entropy-based fitness function of the rule set associated to d, over the isokinetic curves sample set "features".

Specified by:

Overrides:
fitness in class GggpImpl
Parameters:
individuals - The derivations with the rule set associated to each one.
features - The sample set of isokinetic curves.
parameters - The extra-parameters associated to the function.
Returns:
A map with the fitness of each individual (the individuals are the key of the map).

train

public java.util.Collection<Derivation> train(java.lang.String fileGrammar,
                                              java.lang.String fileFeaturesTotal,
                                              java.lang.String fileFeaturesTrain,
                                              int cols,
                                              int sizeP,
                                              int maxDepth,
                                              java.lang.String symbol,
                                              int symbol2,
                                              int K,
                                              int perBest,
                                              boolean elitism,
                                              int amountIter,
                                              double percentage,
                                              boolean applyEnt)
                                       throws GggpExceptionImpl
Parameters:
fileGrammar - The path and name of the file with the Grammar's definition.
fileFeaturesTotal - The path and name of the file with the features in order to calculate the initial values for the initial population.
fileFeaturesTrain - The path and name of the file with the features in order to train the GGGP system.
cols - The column's amount of fileFeatures (18).
sizeP - The GGGP System's size population (200).
maxDepth - Maximum Depth of the Derivations (10).
symbol - The Element's symbol to which the Evolutionary Gradient will be applied ("real").
symbol2 - The Element's symbol which has the name of the feature, for which the Evolutionary Gradient is looking for a real value that will be used in a rule ("TV1").
K - The parameter used in the Tournament operator.
perBest - If elitism'll be applied, the parameters defines which percentage of the current generation'll survive in the next (the survivals are selected by theirs fitness,ie, only the individuals with the best fitness are selected).
elitism - It defines if elitism is applied or not.
amountIter - It defines the maximum amount of training's iterations.
percentage - It defines the maximum fitness to be reached, ie, if the training process reach this fitness the process is stopped.
applyEnt - It defines if apply Entropy or not in the fitness calculation.
Returns:
The Derivation (the best individual) that results from the training process.
Throws:
GggpExceptionImpl
